'''Nokia Suite''' (formerly '''Nokia Ovi Suite''') is an application for [[Nokia]] users to connect their devices with [[Microsoft Windows]].
==Overview== Nokia Suite can synchronize contacts, calendar, messages, photos, videos and music between a Nokia device and a PC. Additionally, Nokia Suite can download country maps to Nokia devices, backup or restore the contents of devices,<ref>{{Cite web |url = http://europe.nokia.com/support/download-software/nokia-ovi-suite/howto/synchronise-and-back-up-your-information |title = Synchronise and back up your information |work = Nokia Europe website |publisher = Nokia |accessdate = 7 December 2010 }}</ref> connect the PC to the Internet via mobile device ([[tethering]])<ref>{{Cite web |url = http://europe.nokia.com/support/download-software/nokia-ovi-suite/howto/connect-your-computer-to-the-web-with-nokia-ovi-suite |title = Connect your computer to the web with Nokia Ovi Suite |work = Nokia Europe website |publisher = Nokia |accessdate = 7 December 2010 }} </ref> and update the device software.<ref>{{Cite web |url = http://europe.nokia.com/support/download-software/nokia-ovi-suite/howto/download-and-install-new-software |title = Download and install new software and applications |work = Nokia Europe website |publisher = Nokia |accessdate = 7 December 2010 }}</ref>
Nokia Suite is a replacement for [[Nokia PC Suite]]<ref>{{Cite web |url = http://europe.nokia.com/support/download-software/nokia-ovi-suite/faq#00 |title = Nokia Ovi Suite - FAQ |work = Nokia Europe website |publisher = Nokia |accessdate = 7 December 2010 }}</ref> and is integrated with the ''[[Ovi (Nokia)|Ovi]]'' brand of services. It was originally known as ''Nokia Ovi Suite, but the name changed to ''Nokia Suite'' with the release of version 3.2.64 Beta in October 2011.<ref>{{cite web |title=Nokia Suite 3.2 Beta for Windows |url=http://betalabs.nokia.com/node/12390/ |work=Nokia Beta Labs |publisher=Nokia |accessdate=11 November 2011 |author=Samuli |date=31 October 2011 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Nokia Suite (formerly Nokia Ovi Suite) 3.2.100 - Changelog|url=http://www.softpedia.com/progChangelog/Nokia-Ovi-Suite-Changelog-131674.html|work=Softpedia|publisher=SoftNews NET SRL|accessdate=11 November 2011|date=1 November 2011}}</ref>
Nokia Suite can perform a complete backup of the phone contents to a single file with .nbu [[filename extension]]. The only official way to gain access to the contents of the backup is to restore it to the phone using Nokia Suite. However, there are third-party programs that can read these files with some success, like the [[open-source software]] ''NBU Explorer'' <ref>{{Cite web |url = http://sourceforge.net/projects/nbuexplorer/ |title = NBU Explorer |work = [[SourceForge]] |publisher = SourceForge |accessdate = 7 December 2010 }}</ref> and the shareware [[Noki]].
